text: Mariana Muci Torres (born 15 February 1988) is a Venezuelan former professional tennis player. Muci grew up in the Venezuelan city of Valencia, but was born in Lebanon. A right-handed player, she featured in a total of 12 ties for the Venezuela Fed Cup team, the first in 2004. She also represented Venezuela in Central American and Caribbean Games and Pan American Games competition. At the 2006 Central American and Caribbean Games she won a gold medal in the women's doubles.
